Look at this plastic nonsense.

00:37.000 --> 00:38.700
Only the best places for lunch.

00:38.700 --> 00:39.930
Taco-eating contest, man.

00:39.940 --> 00:41.500
Who's having
a taco-eating contest?

00:41.500 --> 00:43.240
-Keenan and tony.
-The two skinny guys?

00:43.240 --> 00:45.170
-That's a great idea.
-Yes.

00:45.170 --> 00:47.410
Okay, well,
I got 100 bucks on it.

00:47.410 --> 00:49.410
-A hundred bucks for what?
-Who can eat the most tacos.

00:49.410 --> 00:50.480
-I'm following.
-We need to get in on this.

00:50.480 --> 00:51.780
I'm in on this.
Yeah.

00:51.780 --> 00:54.110
When you finish a taco,
taco.

00:54.120 --> 00:56.920
Wow.
But maybe not so hard.

00:56.920 --> 00:58.590
So you ready?
All right.

00:58.590 --> 01:00.550
Go. Oh, my god.
[ russell slaps table ]

01:00.560 --> 01:04.990
russell stuck a whole taco
in his mouth.

01:04.990 --> 01:06.760
How big is your mouth?

01:06.760 --> 01:08.400
-Taco.
-You got to yell out taco.

01:08.400 --> 01:10.500
Taco!

01:10.500 --> 01:12.300
He's at six.
Russell is at six.

01:12.300 --> 01:15.300
-Taco.
-Russell is at seven.

01:15.300 --> 01:17.440
-[ mouthful speech ] four.
-Mike's got four.

01:17.440 --> 01:20.070
Keke got seven.
Oh, my god.

01:20.080 --> 01:23.110
You just drank the flower water.
-I'm waving the flag.

01:23.110 --> 01:24.380
Christie: I think keke's going
to throw up.

01:24.380 --> 01:27.920
-That's it.
-And russell has 11.

01:27.920 --> 01:29.020
Make that 12.

01:29.020 --> 01:30.680
Russell hands down wins.

01:30.690 --> 01:33.220
You are the proud recipient
of richard's money.

01:33.220 --> 01:34.420
For the first time ever.

01:34.420 --> 01:35.690
-Ever.
-Good for you, russell.

01:35.690 --> 01:37.990
-Congratulations, russell.
-Awesome job. Awesome.

01:37.990 --> 01:41.430
All the monkeys
for a really good lunch.

01:41.430 --> 01:42.830
-Oh.
-And you settle up?

01:42.830 --> 01:44.970
Man: Thanks, russell.

01:44.970 --> 01:47.130
They didn't pay.
I'm stuck with the bill?

01:47.140 --> 01:48.600
Oh, my god.
Ring me up.

01:48.600 --> 01:50.300
Thanks, guys.

01:50.310 --> 01:51.770
[ whoosh ]
[ tires squeal ]

01:51.770 --> 01:53.440
[ laughs ]
whoo!

01:53.440 --> 01:55.910
-Right now, on "fast n' loud"...
-Boom!

01:55.910 --> 01:58.210
Narrator: ...Hot rod hunter
richard rawlings

01:58.210 --> 01:59.680
and the gas monkey crew...

01:59.680 --> 02:00.950
I don't give a [bleep]
about style.

02:00.950 --> 02:02.650
That's a great answer.
We'll stick with that.

02:02.650 --> 02:04.220
Narrator:
...Are making a splash.

02:04.220 --> 02:05.850
Hate to even think
what richard's done on this.

02:05.860 --> 02:09.060
But transforming richard's
mustang from roadkill...

02:09.060 --> 02:10.690
I'm the one that looks like
it's on fire.

02:10.690 --> 02:13.530
...To the star of a
mega-million-dollar shelby show.

02:13.530 --> 02:15.400
Four hundred fifteen
horsepower?

02:15.400 --> 02:18.330
Yes, sir. When there's a traffic
jam, I'm like, "suckers."

02:18.330 --> 02:20.330
and then...
This is freaking sick.

02:20.340 --> 02:22.100
That's my [bleep] man.

02:22.100 --> 02:25.310
...Richard finds a mopar
monument to '70s glam...

02:25.310 --> 02:27.110
Twenty-five g's, bro.

02:27.110 --> 02:28.610
...That might leave him
in the red.

02:28.610 --> 02:30.080
Man: So what are you looking
to get for it?

02:30.080 --> 02:32.680
About $20,000.
I was thinking $7,500.

02:32.680 --> 02:34.010
Whoa.

