captions paid for by
discovery communications

02:42.320 --> 02:45.660
richard: At gas monkey, we've
built dozens of iconic cars.

02:45.660 --> 02:46.990
It all started
with a little garage

02:47.000 --> 02:49.600
where we built the model a.

02:49.600 --> 02:52.300
There's so many cars
that I hated to see go:

02:52.300 --> 02:54.430
The hot wheels corvette...

02:54.440 --> 02:56.500
Oh, the midas monkey.

02:56.510 --> 02:57.800
[ engine revs ]

02:57.810 --> 03:00.240
the ferrari f-40 we resurrected
and painted black,

03:00.240 --> 03:02.140
[ engine revs ]

03:03.680 --> 03:06.410
and the '49 chevy pickup we took
the lone star throw down.

03:06.420 --> 03:11.020
Awesome builds that have made
the gas monkey brand what it is.

03:11.020 --> 03:13.150
But my '68 mustang
came before them all.

03:13.160 --> 03:15.690
She's my first love,
and I'm never letting her go.

03:15.690 --> 03:17.690
In fact, in a few weeks,
I'm taking it to one

03:17.690 --> 03:19.530
of the longest-running
mustang car shows.

03:19.530 --> 03:22.530
It's a big deal, the mid america
shelby meet in tulsa.

03:22.530 --> 03:24.400
It's high-profile
in the ford world

03:24.400 --> 03:26.200
and a perfect place
to show off this car

03:26.200 --> 03:27.800
and the gas monkey brand.

03:27.800 --> 03:30.600
[ hissing ]

03:30.610 --> 03:32.210
[ cell phone rings ]

03:32.210 --> 03:34.440
oh.
Hey, what's going on?

03:34.440 --> 03:36.540
You know when I take my mustang
out for a perfect day

03:36.550 --> 03:37.950
and it all goes to [bleep]?

03:37.950 --> 03:39.410
<i> That's today.</i>

03:39.420 --> 03:42.080
<i> I'm on the side of the road.</i>
About 3 miles from the shop.

03:42.080 --> 03:43.350
You can't miss me.

03:43.350 --> 03:44.650
I'm the one that looks like
it's on fire.

03:44.650 --> 03:46.190
<i> Well, it's a great day</i>
<i> in the neighborhood.</i>

03:46.190 --> 03:48.620
<i> See you in a minute.</i>
[ bleep ].

03:48.620 --> 03:51.590
All right.
Let's see how bad it is.

03:51.590 --> 03:53.130
It looked like he
lost something.

03:53.130 --> 03:55.300
-Yeah.
-What'd I lose over there?

03:55.300 --> 03:57.630
-A bunch of green fluid.
-Have to cool it.

03:57.630 --> 03:58.900
I'm pretty sure the heater core
is blown because

03:58.900 --> 04:00.270
the floor is wet, but...
-Oh, okay.

04:00.270 --> 04:01.700
...I'm pretty sure the motor
is shot too, so...

04:01.700 --> 04:03.070
The good news is,
it's a small block four.

04:03.070 --> 04:04.670
The car needs
to be gone through.

04:04.670 --> 04:06.370
Let's just get it to the shop
and see what we're looking at.

04:06.380 --> 04:07.410
Let's just load it up.

04:07.410 --> 04:08.640
-All right.
-Get it back to the shop.

04:08.640 --> 04:10.010
Y'all pull the ramps.
I'll drive it up there.

04:10.010 --> 04:11.280
It's not like
I'm going to hurt it.

04:11.280 --> 04:13.250
[ clanking ]

04:15.720 --> 04:17.920
whoa.
That sounds like [bleep], guys.

04:17.920 --> 04:21.660
The good news is, we don't have
to push it up on the trailer.

04:21.660 --> 04:23.790
He's in a pretty good mood for
a guy who just blew up his car.

04:23.790 --> 04:25.530
[ tires squeal ]

04:28.660 --> 04:31.530
we're not immune to auto failure
at gas monkey garage.

04:31.530 --> 04:33.370
My favorite mustang,
the motor got a little hot,

04:33.370 --> 04:36.070
and I think that blew
the heater core.

04:36.070 --> 04:38.410
I'm actually happy it happened,
so now we've got some time

04:38.410 --> 04:40.310
to give it the love it deserves
before it represents

04:40.310 --> 04:43.140
gas monkey at the big
shelby meet in tulsa.

04:43.150 --> 04:44.480
It's time to go through it
front to back.

04:44.480 --> 04:45.750
I don't think we should
let him drive.

04:45.750 --> 04:47.810
Going to chauffeur you
around now.

04:47.820 --> 04:49.550
Oh, right on.
I'm down.

04:49.550 --> 04:52.350
Why does it smell like bengay
and old fast food in here?

04:52.350 --> 04:53.820
Ask mater.

04:53.820 --> 04:56.520
Y'all know this mustang is one
of my favorite cars.

04:56.530 --> 04:59.190
It's a replica of the one
they used in the 1999 version

04:59.190 --> 05:00.630
of "the thomas crown affair."

05:00.630 --> 05:03.200
it wasn't a real shelby,
but they made it look like one,

05:03.200 --> 05:04.530
and that's hollywood for you.

05:04.530 --> 05:06.070
It was in the movie
for less than 2 minutes

05:06.070 --> 05:08.270
but left a lasting impression
on mustang lovers

05:08.270 --> 05:12.040
with its mix of muscle
and off-road style.

05:12.040 --> 05:14.880
Jay riecke paid me $85,000
to take a stock mustang

05:14.880 --> 05:16.880
and make it look
just like the one in the show,

05:16.880 --> 05:18.580
and that was about
10 years ago.

05:18.580 --> 05:21.150
But I ended up getting it back
from him, and I'm glad I did.

05:21.150 --> 05:23.850
It's my sentimental favorite.

05:23.850 --> 05:26.350
Looks like a small block ford.

05:26.360 --> 05:28.790
I know it was blowing a lot
of steam out of the ac vents,

05:28.790 --> 05:32.790
but I don't think
it's just a heater core.

05:32.800 --> 05:35.630
It's a movie car, so it's got
its own following.

05:35.630 --> 05:36.630
-It is unique...
-Yeah.

05:36.630 --> 05:37.800
...If nothing else.
Yep.

05:37.800 --> 05:39.130
And it's known worldwide, so,
you know,

05:39.130 --> 05:40.800
it does represent
the gas monkey brand.

05:40.800 --> 05:42.600
What's it looking like so far?

05:42.600 --> 05:44.670
It's looking like
a blown small block ford to me.

05:44.670 --> 05:46.740
-How'd the water look?
-Kind of green, kind of brown.

05:46.740 --> 05:48.280
We decided you got your money's
worth out of this one.

05:48.280 --> 05:49.380
-Yeah.
-All right.

05:49.380 --> 05:51.380
Just yank it.
Snap in, snap out, man.

05:51.380 --> 05:53.250
My guys at the racetrack do this
in like 45 minutes.

05:53.250 --> 05:54.450
Yeah. This isn't quite
the same thing.

05:54.450 --> 05:56.680
I'm pretty sure
it's pretty different.

05:56.690 --> 05:58.250
Richard: With the mid american
shelby meet coming up,

05:58.250 --> 05:59.820
the time is right
to make my favorite car

05:59.820 --> 06:01.390
better than it's ever been,

06:01.390 --> 06:03.860
and besides, it hasn't run
the same since george foreman

06:03.860 --> 06:05.490
took it out for a joyride.

06:05.490 --> 06:07.360
Suckers!

06:07.360 --> 06:09.600
[ tires squeal, engine revs ]

06:09.600 --> 06:12.500
[ laughter ]

06:12.500 --> 06:14.630
now is the perfect time
to make the car a star again.

06:14.640 --> 06:16.000
I can get a big marketing boost

06:16.000 --> 06:18.470
showing it at the shelby meet,
and I've got jason.

06:18.470 --> 06:21.040
He's an honest-to-god
mustang resto expert.

06:21.040 --> 06:23.080
Hell, he's even going to be
judging the restorations

06:23.080 --> 06:25.050
up at the show in tulsa.

06:25.050 --> 06:27.310
So that's a win-win.
The car gets fixed,

06:27.320 --> 06:28.950
gas monkey gets
a big brand boost,

06:28.950 --> 06:31.120
and I get to drink some beer and
look at some other cool cars.

06:31.120 --> 06:33.990
The car's relatively solid,
but everything inside here

06:33.990 --> 06:36.160
and underneath needs
to be redone.

06:36.160 --> 06:37.420
Jason: So new motor,
transmission.

06:37.430 --> 06:39.560
The engine bay needs to be
clean, all new hardware.

06:39.560 --> 06:40.960
We need to get rid
of all this crap

06:40.960 --> 06:43.400
and make it look
traditional under the hood.

06:43.400 --> 06:45.030
We've got it torn open,
let's fix everything

06:45.030 --> 06:46.200
we need to fix.
That's right.

06:46.200 --> 06:48.400
If we're going to do it,
let's just do it now.

06:50.740 --> 06:52.740
Now is the time to return
by thomas crown

06:52.740 --> 06:54.540
mustang to stardom.

06:54.540 --> 06:57.180
We're going to replace the blown
engine with a 347 stroker

06:57.180 --> 06:59.350
with a monster
overdrive transmission.

06:59.350 --> 07:00.710
Then we'll add a ron davis
radiator

07:00.720 --> 07:02.180
to take care
of my overheating problems

07:02.180 --> 07:05.590
that got all this started
in the first place.

07:05.590 --> 07:07.050
The guys will go through
the drivetrain,

07:07.060 --> 07:09.120
put in wilwood brakes and make
sure it's blowing cold air

07:09.120 --> 07:11.960
with a unit from vintage ac
because it's texas.

07:11.960 --> 07:13.460
I don't want to be hot.

07:13.460 --> 07:15.130
The mustang meet
is in just 2 weeks,

07:15.130 --> 07:16.760
but they've already announced
I'm bringing the car,

07:16.770 --> 07:18.430
so there's no pushing
the deadline.

07:18.430 --> 07:20.630
As long as the guys
stick to the $15,000 budget,

07:20.640 --> 07:23.670
it'll be worth every penny
to show off the car at the meet.

07:23.670 --> 07:25.770
It's my car, so do it right.

07:25.770 --> 07:27.610
-We won't get crazy.
-All right.

07:27.610 --> 07:29.210
That's 2 weeks and a few days

07:29.210 --> 07:32.480
because you got to be up
there early, so I need it done.

07:32.480 --> 07:34.780
I'm going to see another piece
of history up in chicago.

07:34.780 --> 07:36.350
Y'all take care of my baby.

07:36.350 --> 07:43.390
♪

07:43.390 --> 07:46.130
it's a miserable day in chicago
with snow on the ground,

07:46.130 --> 07:48.930
but it's not as bad
as minnesota, so I'll take that.

07:48.930 --> 07:50.300
[ dog barks ]

07:50.300 --> 07:51.930
a while back, my buddy
dennis bought a rare

07:51.930 --> 07:53.830
mustang from a dude
who lived near chicago

07:53.840 --> 07:55.600
in the town of naperville.

07:55.600 --> 07:57.370
Dennis tipped me off to the fact
that this guy had

07:57.370 --> 08:00.240
a one-of-a-kind van
that had pretty amazing history.

08:00.240 --> 08:01.840
Now, dennis knows one-of-a-kind,

08:01.840 --> 08:04.710
and I dig automotive history,
so I'm here to check it out.

08:04.710 --> 08:06.210
[ doorbell rings ]

08:06.220 --> 08:07.280
what's going on, sir?

08:07.280 --> 08:08.820
What's up, dude?
Richard rawlings.

08:08.820 --> 08:09.920
Tom burke.
How are you?

08:09.920 --> 08:11.320
My name is thomas burke.

08:11.320 --> 08:13.520
I currently live in naperville.
I'm from downers grove.

08:13.520 --> 08:14.960
Is it in here?
It is.

08:14.960 --> 08:16.620
Let's check it out.
Let me go open the door and...

08:16.630 --> 08:17.960
Richard:
Tom is a mopar fanatic,

08:17.960 --> 08:20.830
and he actually has
mr. Norm's ramcharger van.

08:20.830 --> 08:23.360
Now, mr. Norm here
in the chicago area

08:23.370 --> 08:26.670
was literally mr. Mopar.

08:26.670 --> 08:28.600
Mr. Norm had a dodge dealership
in chicago

08:28.600 --> 08:31.070
back in the '60s and '70s
and became a huge success

08:31.070 --> 08:33.240
selling high-performance parts
and cars.

08:33.240 --> 08:36.240
He was a customizer of sorts,
a tuner of sorts.

08:36.250 --> 08:39.280
He was way before his time.

08:39.280 --> 08:41.050
And so to get a piece
of history

08:41.050 --> 08:43.950
that's directly related to him
would be pretty cool

08:43.950 --> 08:46.690
and potentially very lucrative.

08:46.690 --> 08:49.760
Super rad.

08:49.760 --> 08:51.860
Here's a piece
of freaking history.

08:51.860 --> 08:53.190
It's a van.

08:53.200 --> 08:54.660
It's called a maxi van,

08:54.660 --> 08:57.860
so it's got the extra piece
on the back with the window.

08:57.870 --> 08:59.330
The paint job is just supercool.

08:59.330 --> 09:01.500
I mean, to know that they did
that back when this was built,

09:01.500 --> 09:03.100
that was an actual race car,
and they stretched it

09:03.110 --> 09:05.070
to make it look like
it was going down the road.

09:05.070 --> 09:08.140
I mean, the '70s
were crazy, man.

09:08.140 --> 09:09.540
I had my eye on it
for years.

09:09.550 --> 09:11.980
My neighbor owned it, and it
took me like 12 years to get it.

09:11.980 --> 09:13.310
This is freaking sick.

09:13.320 --> 09:14.810
So we're talking about it,
and, you know,

09:14.820 --> 09:16.250
there was a lady
that painted the mural.

09:16.250 --> 09:18.220
It was an actual car
that was racing at the time.

09:18.220 --> 09:22.020
In 1977, mr. Norm had this
built to commemorate the car.

09:22.020 --> 09:23.990
It's got a 440 and a dana.
Yeah.

09:23.990 --> 09:25.460
So he ordered it
a little bit special.

09:25.460 --> 09:26.630
You bet.
Yeah.

09:26.630 --> 09:27.860
Richard:
The 440 engine was unique

09:27.860 --> 09:29.700
for its web-shaped
combustion chambers.

09:29.700 --> 09:33.130
The dana 60 axle was also used
on the challenger and the cuda,

09:33.140 --> 09:35.900
so combined up,
it's a classic muscle-car setup.

09:35.900 --> 09:37.000
There's mr. Norm.

09:37.010 --> 09:38.370
He signed it right here.
No kidding.

09:38.370 --> 09:40.710
When I brought it
to the belvidere car show

09:40.710 --> 09:43.840
2 years ago, I saw him,
and he started going like this.

09:43.850 --> 09:45.610
He started shaking,
and he's goes,

09:45.610 --> 09:47.280
"that's my [bleep] van.

09:47.280 --> 09:49.120
Where the [bleep]
did you find it?"

09:49.120 --> 09:51.050
it's pretty dagum nice interior
and everything.

09:51.050 --> 09:52.450
It's in good shape.

09:52.450 --> 09:54.090
I was really expecting to find
a lot of rust on the van,

09:54.090 --> 09:55.420
and it's not rusty.

09:55.420 --> 09:58.330
For being up here, this is
considered, like, perfect.

09:58.330 --> 09:59.560
So we're going to take it
for a ride,

09:59.560 --> 10:00.690
but I need to know
where our starting point is.

10:00.700 --> 10:02.800
What do you want for it?
Twenty-five gs, bro.

10:02.800 --> 10:04.430
Whoo.
Yeah.

10:04.430 --> 10:06.030
Okay, let's...
Yeah, I'm not committing

10:06.030 --> 10:07.300
to that,
but let's take it for a ride

10:07.300 --> 10:09.240
because it is a cool
piece of history.

10:11.240 --> 10:13.310
Steering feels good.
Brakes feel good.

10:13.310 --> 10:15.280
I mean, I think you could drive
this thing back to dallas.

10:15.280 --> 10:16.410
You probably could.

10:16.410 --> 10:18.750
Norm wanted to take it
to canada.

10:18.750 --> 10:20.080
This thing is rad, man.

10:20.080 --> 10:22.080
I mean, it does everything
it's supposed to do.

10:22.080 --> 10:23.250
I'm very impressed.

10:23.250 --> 10:25.750
It runs, drives, starts,
stops pretty much

10:25.750 --> 10:27.620
impeccably,
like it's brand-new.

10:27.620 --> 10:30.220
I really believe that I could
drive it back to dallas.

10:30.230 --> 10:31.890
All right, dude.

10:31.890 --> 10:33.990
It actually runs and drive
pretty dagum nice.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.500
It does, doesn't it?

10:35.500 --> 10:39.670
I just...Man.

10:39.670 --> 10:41.370
I can't do 25,000 grand.

10:41.370 --> 10:42.570
I mean, what...
That's a little high.

10:42.570 --> 10:43.800
Why is it...
Why you got it priced so high?

10:43.810 --> 10:45.010
Even with the history,
it's a little high.

10:45.010 --> 10:46.940
I think it's worth
more like $10,000.

10:46.940 --> 10:48.110
[ scoffs ] yeah.

10:48.110 --> 10:50.540
I mean, because if it was just
a regular tradesman,

10:50.550 --> 10:52.510
it would be worth
$2,000.

10:52.510 --> 10:55.020
Look at what it's got, a 440,
a dana,

10:55.020 --> 10:56.720
just synonymous with mopar.

10:56.720 --> 10:57.980
You're going to definitely
have to come up

10:57.990 --> 10:59.850
if you're going to take
this thing home to texas.

10:59.860 --> 11:02.090
We're going to have to work
on that 10 number, dude.

11:02.090 --> 11:04.260
How about $15,000?

11:04.260 --> 11:06.060
I'm thinking more like
$20,000, dude.

11:06.060 --> 11:07.690
How about 16?

11:11.970 --> 11:13.670
As long as you got the money
with you...

11:13.670 --> 11:14.870
[bleep] yeah.
...We'll do $16,000, man.

11:14.870 --> 11:16.040
Let's do it.
Cool, man.

11:16.040 --> 11:17.770
I think I might have just set
the world record

11:17.770 --> 11:19.770
for a tradesman 200.

11:19.780 --> 11:21.010
Besides the performance package,

11:21.010 --> 11:22.910
custom interior,
and that crazy mural,

11:22.910 --> 11:26.280
what's really special about
this van is, it was mr. Norm's,

11:26.280 --> 11:28.720
and I can take that
and sell it for a profit.

11:28.720 --> 11:30.220
Let's go in, do some paperwork
and then...

11:30.220 --> 11:31.380
-Cool.
-...I got to figure out

11:31.390 --> 11:32.550
how to get this thing
shipped down there.

11:32.550 --> 11:34.790
It's awful big.
Yeah.

11:34.790 --> 11:36.320
[ whoosh ]
[ tires squeal ]

11:36.320 --> 11:37.960
-whoo!
-Coming up on "fast n' loud"...

11:37.960 --> 11:39.360
What are y'all doing to my baby?

11:39.360 --> 11:41.130
-...The pressure is on...
-This might be real bad.

11:41.130 --> 11:43.930
Narrator:
...To rebuild richard's crown
jewel and...

11:43.930 --> 11:46.570
Russell!
How was my russell impression?

11:46.570 --> 11:49.000
...Rustling up a buyer
for the mr. Norm van.

11:49.000 --> 11:50.840
Somehow I got to
keep you employed.

12:02.580 --> 12:04.020
This should all look
like a shelby.

12:04.020 --> 12:05.120
You know, it's not...
-I agree.

12:05.120 --> 12:06.220
-Right now it really doesn't.
-Yeah.

12:06.220 --> 12:07.650
Any fabrication
for this thing or no?

12:07.660 --> 12:08.920
There's a little bit.

12:08.920 --> 12:10.060
We're going to have to refit
a new grille.

12:10.060 --> 12:11.060
I think that's the idea,
is everything needs

12:11.060 --> 12:12.330
to look like a shelby.

12:12.330 --> 12:13.560
Even though it's not
a real shelby,

12:13.560 --> 12:15.260
we want it to look like one.

12:15.260 --> 12:16.730
The moviemakers weren't about
to tear up

12:16.730 --> 12:18.100
an actual shelby for the film.

12:18.100 --> 12:19.300
That would have been
a waste of money,

12:19.300 --> 12:20.600
and in true hollywood style,

12:20.600 --> 12:22.770
richard started
with a stand-in too.

12:22.770 --> 12:25.670
His is a '68 gta convertible.

12:25.670 --> 12:27.770
Richard's got
a mixed tape.

12:27.780 --> 12:28.840
-Oh, boy.
-Oh, yeah?

12:28.840 --> 12:30.040
-Let me grab that.
-What's on it?

12:30.050 --> 12:31.410
Barry white.

12:31.410 --> 12:33.150
The car really is
a gas monkey icon,

12:33.150 --> 12:34.550
and working on it means
uncovering relics

12:34.550 --> 12:37.980
from richard's
colorful past.

12:37.990 --> 12:39.320
It's really gross.

12:39.320 --> 12:40.420
Hate to even think
what richard's done on this.

12:40.420 --> 12:41.520
It's a dirty pony.

12:41.520 --> 12:43.520
This might be real bad.

12:43.530 --> 12:44.960
Normally we'd just tear
everything out of the car,

12:44.960 --> 12:46.290
but we had to be careful

12:46.290 --> 12:47.830
because we're not changing
everything on this car.

12:47.830 --> 12:50.160
So what's with these stripes
on the driveshaft?

12:50.170 --> 12:53.030
Is that, like, striped socks,
like a team thing?

12:53.030 --> 12:54.170
Back in the day before robots,

12:54.170 --> 12:55.500
they painted stripes
on the driveshaft

12:55.500 --> 12:57.440
to indicate which options
were going on the car...

12:57.440 --> 12:58.870
Oh, yay.

12:58.870 --> 13:00.370
...Like which transmission
or if it had air conditioning,

13:00.380 --> 13:02.510
so workers could tell
at a glance what to install.

13:02.510 --> 13:03.580
Man: You got it.

13:03.580 --> 13:05.850
Wait a minute.
Ta-da.

13:05.850 --> 13:07.510
Whoa.
That goes really fast.

13:07.520 --> 13:08.820
The 9-inch rear end
is one of ford's

13:08.820 --> 13:10.320
most popular,
so we're keeping that.

13:10.320 --> 13:12.820
I was wondering
why it came on it.

13:12.820 --> 13:15.050
Brian:
And hot rodders, they love
the aluminum c4 transmission

13:15.060 --> 13:16.420
because it's 40 pounds lighter

13:16.420 --> 13:18.830
than the older cast-iron ones,
but it can't handle

13:18.830 --> 13:20.290
the 400-horsepower
from this new engine,

13:20.300 --> 13:21.660
so this whole trans
has got to go.

13:21.660 --> 13:22.730
C4s aren't bad.
Mnh!

13:22.730 --> 13:25.300
Got your finger?
Yep.

13:25.300 --> 13:26.300
All right.
Ready to go down, guys?

13:26.300 --> 13:27.430
Yep.

13:27.440 --> 13:28.870
Brian: Next, it's time
to pull the motor.

13:28.870 --> 13:29.970
This could get messy.

13:29.970 --> 13:31.810
Yeah, it's leaking a little bit.
[ laughs ]

13:31.810 --> 13:33.610
getting a river
of antifreeze.

13:33.610 --> 13:36.510
-You're killing me.
-A river of coolant.

13:36.510 --> 13:38.650
-Look at that.
-Pretty gross.

13:38.650 --> 13:40.150
This is not the first time
it's saturated.

13:40.150 --> 13:42.220
That thing has been saturated
so many times.

13:42.220 --> 13:44.450
What are y'all doing
to my baby?

13:44.450 --> 13:47.420
We're making it much nicer.

13:47.420 --> 13:49.620
Holy cow, man.

13:49.620 --> 13:51.360
It's like mice on cheese.

13:51.360 --> 13:52.730
-Yep.
-All right.

13:52.730 --> 13:55.030
Mustang, this is going to
hurt me more than it hurts you,

13:55.030 --> 13:56.700
but if we're going to take you
to the mid america shelby

13:56.700 --> 13:59.470
meet up in oklahoma, then we got
to get you in tip-top shape.

13:59.470 --> 14:01.000
I love this car,
and there's going to be

14:01.000 --> 14:02.270
a lot of eyeballs on it.

14:02.270 --> 14:03.640
It's never really been shown.

14:03.640 --> 14:06.570
This needs to be my statement
piece for another 10, 12 years

14:06.580 --> 14:07.640
like it has been.

14:07.640 --> 14:08.680
When she's put back together,
this car

14:08.680 --> 14:09.980
will have
a lot of the similar bells

14:09.980 --> 14:11.510
and whistles
of an original shelby,

14:11.510 --> 14:13.810
but you won't be afraid
to drive it like you stole it.

14:13.820 --> 14:17.580
A real restored shelby like this
would go for upwards of 500k.

14:17.590 --> 14:19.190
This will have the look
and feel of one

14:19.190 --> 14:20.620
but at a tenth of the cost.

14:20.620 --> 14:23.790
Who wouldn't want that?

14:23.790 --> 14:26.090
I almost have a tear in my eye
seeing this car torn apart.

14:26.090 --> 14:27.130
Look away.
Hey. Look away.

14:27.130 --> 14:28.230
I'm going to get back
to my office.

14:28.230 --> 14:29.330
Two weeks you'll be
the happiest guy.

14:29.330 --> 14:30.460
Yeah, I promise.

14:30.470 --> 14:31.800
They'll be happy tears
in 2 weeks.

14:31.800 --> 14:33.600
Better be overjoyed,
and it's less than 2 weeks now.

14:33.600 --> 14:40.070
♪

14:40.080 --> 14:41.670
not in there.

14:41.680 --> 14:47.280
♪

14:47.280 --> 14:48.820
I need a black pen.

14:48.820 --> 14:50.420
Oh, thanks.

14:50.420 --> 14:57.490
♪

14:57.490 --> 15:04.660
♪

15:04.670 --> 15:07.470
check this out. I'm going to do
my best russell impression.

15:07.470 --> 15:09.940
[ imitating russell ]
russell!

15:09.940 --> 15:11.300
Why are you yelling?

15:11.310 --> 15:13.270
How was my
russell impression?

15:13.280 --> 15:15.170
Come here.
I got something for you.

15:15.180 --> 15:17.640
I got this kick-ass van.
It was mr. Norm's.

15:17.650 --> 15:19.450
You ever heard of mr. Norm's
out of the chicago area?

15:19.450 --> 15:22.080
No. There's a guy who
owns a donut shop in
new york named mr. Norm.

15:22.080 --> 15:23.250
No. No. No.

15:23.250 --> 15:24.920
This guy was well-known
in the early '70s

15:24.920 --> 15:27.120
for everything mopar,
super popular dude.

15:27.120 --> 15:29.560
Somewhere along the way,
he decided to build his own van.

15:29.560 --> 15:32.030
It's all tricked out with
a drag car on the side of it,

15:32.030 --> 15:33.530
shag carpets, swivel seats.

15:33.530 --> 15:34.730
Perfect.
You name it.

15:34.730 --> 15:35.830
Well, I need to sell it.

15:35.830 --> 15:37.200
Search the net,
and find me a mr. Norm

15:37.200 --> 15:38.560
fan that wants
to buy this thing.

15:38.570 --> 15:40.000
You think that'll go?
It's a van.

15:40.000 --> 15:41.330
Vans are cool, man.

15:41.340 --> 15:43.400
Richard:
I paid $16,000 for this
mr. Norm's van.

15:43.410 --> 15:44.970
All I need to do is make
a little bit of profit,

15:44.970 --> 15:47.610
so I've got russell, and he
is going to try to turn up

15:47.610 --> 15:50.110
one of the many hordes
of mr. Norm's fans,

15:50.110 --> 15:52.450
and hopefully they got $20,000
or $30,000 in their pocket.

15:52.450 --> 15:54.680
Alright. See if there's any
action on the web.

15:54.680 --> 15:55.920
Somehow I got to
keep you employed.

15:55.920 --> 15:57.580
There's a whole building
and a kitchen

15:57.590 --> 15:58.820
and all these projects.

15:58.820 --> 16:00.450
Can I use the van
as a work van?

16:00.460 --> 16:02.360
Oh, absolutely not.
We're selling it for profit.

16:02.360 --> 16:04.060
Damn it.

16:08.760 --> 16:11.260
-What do you got there?
-Hitch a ride here.

16:11.270 --> 16:12.500
Got y'all an engine.

16:12.500 --> 16:13.930
So our '68
mustang needs a new motor.

16:13.940 --> 16:15.900
This thing overheats every time
richard drives it,

16:15.900 --> 16:17.340
so I need to get the new one
out of the box,

16:17.340 --> 16:20.970
see what needs to be painted
and make sure it all matches up.

16:20.980 --> 16:24.510
Open this thing up.
I got y'all a 347 stroker motor.

16:24.510 --> 16:27.010
Really?
So he just had a 302 before.

16:27.020 --> 16:28.350
Jason: I think we got
a major upgrade here.

16:28.350 --> 16:29.820
Figured
he'd want better power.

16:29.820 --> 16:31.580
As if he didn't already burn
the tires off of it enough.

16:31.590 --> 16:32.990
Yeah,
we got it from summit,

16:32.990 --> 16:34.890
so we were able to get it,
like, today.

16:34.890 --> 16:36.690
I like everything except
that ugly distributor.

16:36.690 --> 16:37.920
Yeah. Exactly.

16:37.930 --> 16:39.330
Brian: This motor is just
what the mustang needs.

16:39.330 --> 16:41.290
It's a stroker, which means
the piston stroke is longer,

16:41.300 --> 16:42.560
which allows
for more combustion,

16:42.560 --> 16:43.860
and that means more power.

16:43.870 --> 16:45.830
This motor pushes about
415 horsepower.

16:45.830 --> 16:47.270
It's almost going to
double the power.

16:47.270 --> 16:50.400
Guys like richard buy a lot
of motors, and we know why.

16:50.410 --> 16:52.740
Let's get it on the stand
and ready for paint.

16:57.050 --> 16:59.210
Is that your new boba fett
outfit?

16:59.210 --> 17:00.510
What? What?

17:00.520 --> 17:02.180
No, dude, you know how hot
it's been in there.

17:02.180 --> 17:05.420
This hood, ac respirator.
Aren't you lucky?

17:05.420 --> 17:07.750
So you plug it in, and it blows,
like, cold air.

17:07.760 --> 17:09.060
Could you get me one, too?

17:09.060 --> 17:10.220
Are you jealous?

17:10.230 --> 17:11.920
Well, you know,
there's two of us, right?

17:11.930 --> 17:13.060
Well, you can...
I'll share with you.

17:13.060 --> 17:14.590
I'm not sharing your hood.

17:14.600 --> 17:16.360
I'm not licking it.

17:16.360 --> 17:19.530
Just go paint something.

17:19.530 --> 17:22.840
Jealous.
Stingy.

17:22.840 --> 17:25.740
I hope that [bleep] breaks.

17:25.740 --> 17:27.440
To pretty this ugly beast
up some,

17:27.440 --> 17:29.640
mike: I'll shoot the underside
an engine compartment

17:29.640 --> 17:31.110
while we've got
the motor torn out.

17:31.110 --> 17:33.750
It's just a time crunch
on this one.

17:33.750 --> 17:36.580
If I was painting this car to be
judged like a restored shelby,

17:36.580 --> 17:37.920
we'd take it down
to metal, prime it

17:37.920 --> 17:40.020
and then paint it like
carroll shelby would,

17:40.020 --> 17:42.820
but we're building
it to be driven, not judged.

17:42.820 --> 17:44.590
The goal is to make it
presentable,

17:44.590 --> 17:47.360
so the undercarriage and engine
bay get a fresh satin black,

17:47.360 --> 17:48.960
and then jason and them
can start stabbing

17:48.960 --> 17:51.600
the new motor
and transmission and all that.

17:51.600 --> 17:56.740
♪

17:56.740 --> 17:58.600
richard:
We hit a critical point
in the riviera build.

17:58.610 --> 18:00.340
I'm investing $300,000
to turn this

18:00.340 --> 18:03.840
1972 land yacht into a super car
to show it off at sema.

18:03.850 --> 18:05.280
All right.

18:05.280 --> 18:08.010
The plan is to make this riviera
look more like a zr1 corvette.

18:08.020 --> 18:09.650
Slam it on a new chassis
and suspension,

18:09.650 --> 18:12.120
and give it bronze wheels
and big tires.

18:12.120 --> 18:14.090
The top gets chopped
for a more aggressive look,

18:14.090 --> 18:16.920
and power, well,
that's a supercharged lt ford

18:16.930 --> 18:18.860
delivering about 1,000 horses.

18:18.860 --> 18:20.230
-Whoa.
-There we go.

18:20.230 --> 18:22.560
The guys have less than 5 months
now to get it all done.

18:22.560 --> 18:24.800
We're just talking about things
that are really time-consuming,

18:24.800 --> 18:26.770
and we're really already
under the gun.

18:26.770 --> 18:29.000
Richard:
Now, while mike coy has got
the mustang in paint,

18:29.000 --> 18:31.200
the guys can make progress
assembling the custom frame

18:31.210 --> 18:33.470
that we got from
chris dawson's chassis works.

18:33.480 --> 18:36.010
Man:
You realize the scale of the car

18:36.010 --> 18:38.140
when you have the chassis
laid out like this.

18:38.150 --> 18:40.450
All this stuff is a little bit
oversized right now too,

18:40.450 --> 18:42.550
just to make sure we had
enough material to cut it in.

18:42.550 --> 18:44.780
Oh, so you'll be able to adjust,
fine-tune everything.

18:44.790 --> 18:45.750
Yes.

18:45.750 --> 18:48.120
How long until the frame
is put together?

18:48.120 --> 18:50.320
Tomorrow.
No. I'm just kidding.

18:50.330 --> 18:52.290
Yeah. That's a great answer.
We'll stick with that.

18:52.290 --> 18:54.930
Let's knock it out.

18:54.930 --> 18:57.060
Josh: The parts are made
to our specifications,

18:57.070 --> 18:58.460
but we have to weld it
all together

18:58.470 --> 19:00.670
and dial it in perfectly
straight and level.

19:00.670 --> 19:02.300
Hit it.
Hit it.

19:06.910 --> 19:09.640
For this super build,
jeremy and I are team fabricate.

19:11.950 --> 19:13.380
The frame,
it's super universal.

19:13.380 --> 19:14.650
Yeah, we have
a front crossmember.

19:14.650 --> 19:16.250
We have the rear independent
all set up.

19:16.250 --> 19:17.880
All the control arms
are figured out.

19:17.890 --> 19:20.690
We just have to kind of put the
pieces together for our needs.

19:20.690 --> 19:23.120
I mean, the car is wider
than most cars.

19:23.120 --> 19:24.590
The car is longer
than most cars,

19:24.590 --> 19:26.830
so chassis works does a great
job about leaving

19:26.830 --> 19:28.160
extra in every direction.

19:28.160 --> 19:30.130
They totally provided us
with what we needed.

19:30.130 --> 19:32.200
It was awesome.
Yeah.

19:32.200 --> 19:33.930
Jeremy: We're really excited
to be building this car,

19:33.940 --> 19:36.400
but with less than 5 months
until sema, for once,

19:36.400 --> 19:39.040
richard may have bit off
more than we can chew.

19:39.040 --> 19:40.540
Everything is a little longer
than it should be,

19:40.540 --> 19:42.380
so we can cut it to size.

19:42.380 --> 19:45.950
I'm just going to chop
the extra off.

19:45.950 --> 19:47.580
I'll add the little brace in.

19:50.220 --> 19:51.450
Set the body on.

19:51.450 --> 19:53.290
Make it to the next step.

19:53.290 --> 19:55.090
Oh, man.

19:55.090 --> 19:57.820
I got to cut the stupid bar
back off.

19:57.830 --> 19:59.330
Geez.

19:59.330 --> 20:00.730
[ whoosh ]
[ tires squeal ]

20:00.730 --> 20:02.760
-whoo!
-Coming up on "fast n' loud"...

20:02.760 --> 20:03.960
Driveshaft,
are you ready for it?

20:03.970 --> 20:05.730
Narrator: ...The shelby build
gets shafted.

20:05.730 --> 20:07.200
It won't quite go
in the yolk.

20:07.200 --> 20:10.770
♪ yeah ♪
and cash cow or white elephant?

20:10.770 --> 20:14.070
Any of the mopar cars, those
things are asking tons of money.

20:14.080 --> 20:17.480
Your van, not so much.

20:28.060 --> 20:29.820
-Chadwick, get the door.
-Door me.

20:29.820 --> 20:31.420
Okay.

20:31.430 --> 20:33.330
Brian: It's a big day
for richard's '68 mustang.

20:33.330 --> 20:35.130
The plan is to get the motor,
transmission and exhaust

20:35.130 --> 20:36.700
all buttoned up
and have the car on the ground

20:36.700 --> 20:38.400
by the end of the day.

20:38.400 --> 20:39.800
Oh, you bastard.

20:39.800 --> 20:40.900
Tony's going to give me a hand
with the brake lines

20:40.900 --> 20:44.400
while the guys stab
the motor.

20:44.410 --> 20:46.010
Mike: It's a small detail,
but choosing the correct

20:46.010 --> 20:48.570
engine paint is vital to keeping
an authentic shelby look.

20:48.580 --> 20:51.410
After 1965, ford committed
to corporate blue engine paint,

20:51.410 --> 20:53.410
so that's what
we're going with.

20:53.410 --> 20:55.350
Wait a minute.
I'm over mine.

20:55.350 --> 20:56.620
Are you over yours?
-Yeah.

20:56.620 --> 20:57.750
Man: Yep.

20:57.750 --> 20:58.750
Jeremy: Those cobra-branded
valve covers,

20:58.750 --> 20:59.920
that's one of those
visual cues

20:59.920 --> 21:02.390
making this mustang
look shelby authentic.

21:02.390 --> 21:06.290
I need to go under to get
the mounting bolts.

21:06.290 --> 21:07.290
All right.

21:07.300 --> 21:08.490
-Perfect.
-Go, team. We did it.

21:08.500 --> 21:09.830
Go fords!

21:09.830 --> 21:12.000
Okay.
Transmission time.

21:14.240 --> 21:15.900
We relied on ford parts
to keep the car looking

21:15.900 --> 21:18.600
cobra authentic,
bonus points if they fit right,

21:18.610 --> 21:20.770
but the monster transmission
is after market,

